                                              Taibbo <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugthanin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gthanin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/10/01 8:08:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> goodluck</span><hr size=1> Sk are one of the best dueling class's, although not its impossible for a rogue to beat a SK in a duel, its very unlikely.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubruke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bruke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/10/01 8:11:11 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: goodluck</span><hr size=1> actually it depends a bit more on gear and ability...jack your resists up over 150 each and he wont land any spells on you except lifetaps.  Save backstabs to time for when hes casting to try and interupt. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/11/01 8:26:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: goodluck</span><hr size=1> A rogue can never beat ANY class that has disabling spells if they cannot resist those spells or get em off quick.   If you don't have good mr I wouldn't bother dueling. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urianne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rianne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/13/01 7:10:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: goodluck</span><hr size=1> MR for fear and snare.  FR and DR for the dots are of lesser importance.<br>
<br>
After all that he can still shadowstep and lifetap you, and drop 1/4-1/3 of your hp with HT.  SK's hurt lots. <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udrevix316.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drevix316</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/15/01 12:28:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re</span><hr size=1> Well..ill give this to you from the SKs point of view. I dueled a 53 rogue with my 52 sk. His MR was 100 or so. So fear kiting was pretty much out of the question. The only spell i could land was my crappy 75 point lifetap..and of course HT. The fight lasted maybe 20 mintues. He had an assassin's BP and managed to get away from me..while i sat and made a pet to keep track of him. I finally won..but barely. He tore me up with his Epic...we both had j/t boots. It was the closest a rogue has ever come to beating me. MR is your best friend in a duel with a SK..trust me.<br>
<br>
Drevix~ <br>
30 rogue Fennin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubayler.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bayler</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/16/01 12:21:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re</span><hr size=1> When the other guy challenges you to a duel, you've got an advantage - you get to pick when it starts.  Depending on how well-prepared your oponent is, you might do something like this:<br>
<br>
1. Apply blinding poison.<br>
2. Sneak behind him, if possible.  If he's alert and/or has his see invis spell on, you won't be able to.<br>
3. Use /disc resistant.  (Fearless doesn't last long enough.)<br>
4. Accept the duel, and immediately backstab and attack to deliver the poison, if possible.<br>
5. While he's blinded, use your Crystallize Pumice to remove all of his buffs.  Important ones are see invis and SoW.  (If he had JBoots, it's just an inconvenience; if he has perm-see invis, the fight is going to suck.)<br>
6. Try Disarm every chance you get. <br>
7. Save backstabs for when he's casting, unless you get solid oppertunities.  <br>
8. If he can't see invis, disengage and hide from time to time.  Keep him guessing about how long you'll be away.  If he's staying on-guard waiting for you, use the time to apply more poison (weaken, dot, dd, paralyzing, whatever), or bind wounds.  If he's using your hide time to do something for himself (like memorize new spells or rebuff himself), punish him with a backstab and then immediately hide again.<br>
<br>
Most of these suggestions rely on gimmiks that an experienced PvPer won't fall for.  But for a casual duel, a sneaky rogue can be very threatening. <p><B>Bayler Briggan Soulblade</B><BR>
48th rank Swashbuckler<BR>
Grandmaster fletcher - Povar-Tarew Artisans<BR>
Xev server<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukeeperofthecows.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keeper of the Cows</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/20/01 3:16:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re</span><hr size=1>  level 60 SK HT hits for1080 dmg in pvp :0( for most 60 rogues  thats over half health in one unresistable insta cast hit :0P they have a 260 dmg lifetap that they can cast every 45 secs or 2 mins? something around there and a 120 dmg lifetap that they can chain cast. They can kill you with unresistable long range damage, which also heals themself(not including HT) so yes, they are pretty tough... not to mention the 12 pt dmg shield can hurt. Root/slow poison is useless on them(shadow step removes the effect). Also about blind poison hurting casters real bad, I use the keyboard for casting most of the time since im lazy and my comp is next to my bed. blindness in no way effects my casting ability when playing my caster chars... so I would go for snare. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=soggee>soggee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/12/01 1:01:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hehe</span><hr size=1> hehe sk's are TOUGH...i love mine  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umavermage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mavermage</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/01 12:17:01 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/maverness/eq000028.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hehe</span><hr size=1>  Sks could arguably be the best class for pvp. At post 50, they get pretty decent dots, lifetaps, and even have shadowstep for a fast escape. The weapons they can use also make them able to deal very significant melee damage. Its just too bad that most SKs depends so heavily upon their HT to kill people. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>The mage formerly known as 
