<p align="center"><font color="#FF0000"><a href="http://companions.windsofstorm.net/">~The Companions~</a><br></font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urazoreyes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Razor Eyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/17/01 2:01:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling a SK</span><hr size=1> No win, unfortunately. Unless you are a -much- better duelist than your opponent is, you're almost certainly toast even before the fight begins. Opening up with a harm touch &amp; a leech -- if both hit, you're in a world of agony. If the leech hits, you just hit. If the leech doesn't hit; how'd you resist it? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
You have to deal with the pets, you have to deal with the boil blood line of spells (hard resist), and the leeches. You have to whittle away ALOT of hps from a high AC target, and deal with them healing themselves through you. The only good news is that clinging darkness/asystole will not land on you, if you have any sort of resists. They can shadowstep, as well.<br>
<br>
Just try to interrupt their spells, go for the backstabs, and get creative in your use of poisons. Your chances, unfortunately, are poor. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhideofulcrum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hideo Fulcrum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/23/01 3:37:06 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.xenogears.org/bb/avatars/XG_Id.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling a SK</span><hr size=1> If you see <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   X is surrounded by an Unholy Aura</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> That lets you know the SK has used their disc which increases Harm Touch damage.  At 60th you'll get hit for 1000+ I'd generally wait until the person was at 50% then use it.  Usually meant death and it doesn't matter if you notice it and run around because the disc lasts a long time.<br>
<br>
If you see <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   X's weapon is surrounded by an eerie blue light</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  Thats 60th level leechcurse disc.  Basically the SK will be healing himself for every hit he lands on you.  So just back off until the disc wears off, it doesn't last long.<br>
<br>
Dmg shields..., SK's have banshee aura, and they might also have the quest ring.  If they're experienced they'll place the DS behind numerous junk buffs.  <br>
<br>
Sk's have numerous options in PVP, one most neglect is the ability to debuff.<br>
<br>
Siphon strength, wave of enfeeblement, shroud of pain, shadow vortex, shroud of hate, and asystole all stack.  That will debuff the target considerably.  They don't do much but the opponent gets a little freaked out with all those spell icons and their str, ac, and agi are all effected.<br>
<br>
Most of the dots while decent are easily resisted by anyone experienced at PVP.  If my opponent was experienced I wouldn't bother with dots.  I'd conserve mana for lifetaps, melee and if I got low I'd shadowstep and lifetap.<br>
<br>
