The only time i won against a sk was lately, we were same level, he had that 280 dmg lifeleech (it does 280 in pvp). Im lvl 55 with epic.<br>
<br>
    Blind poison are useless junk if you want my opinion, i prefer a good old dmg or dot poison even if it means a humble 200 dmg. <br>
<br>
    Well, there i see him and he don't so i apply my berserker madness poison. Hopefully it would reduce his mana pool while doing dd. Drink my sow potion, all self buffs not already up and prepare to use my dead eye discipline wich makes all my swings hit the target.<br>
<br>
    Walk up to him from behind real quick cause at 55 sow potion are way fast while using up discipline. I Open up with normal attack cause poison have better chance to hit him since he sitted and it dont get of on bs wich will make him rise up automatically knowing anyways my bs will hit due to discipline. Poison goes off and stick for 200 dmg.<br>
<br>
     My quad attack collide for average of 60s, so around 320 dmg. Launch my double BS 200 ish 300 ish (500). Another volley of quad attack collide before he get his bearing. He now have been hit for 1340 dmg before knowing what hitted him.  Fight start.<br>
<br>
