</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujorx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jorx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/28/01 9:23:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling a SK</span><hr size=1> I play a SK... and I can tell you what I have experienced in duels over the last 58+ levels...<br>
<br>
Most SK's do NOT use dispel etc.. they rely on Harm Touch to end a battle quickly... ironically those are the SK's you have the best chance at beating..<br>
<br>
I personally try to never use HT in a duel.. that way I always have it, if I really need it.<br>
<br>
MR and DR - get them both up for a duel with a SK, DR is more important if you are fighting 59 or 60 SK.. most people to not have much in the way of DR, and at 59 SK's get Cascading Darkness, a disease based DOT (1000+ pts).<br>
<br>
Many SK's will stand and cast Darkness over and over - wasting mana...  so run around - make them waste their mana..  If their mana is gone, they cant Lifetap...<br>
<br>
I currently have 2 lifetaps loaded at all times, Life Leech (280pts, every 2 mins) and Drain Soul - 226pts that can be chain cast...  <br>
<br>
Best bet to beat a SK... Poison him... then try and BS as much as possible... If you can get him to needing to lifetap to stay alive..  you have a chance.  If the SK has their epic (as I do)... that 250pt lifetap over time on the epic is nasty...  &quot;jousters&quot; hate it...<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uarafain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arafain</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/30/01 2:23:21 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://wootage1.homestead.com/files/aoshi2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling a SK</span><hr size=1> Shadowknights have a lot in common with Necromancers, and not just in their spell lines.  For a shadowknight, a cautious target is a defeated target - with lifetaps, lifetap DOTs, HT, and impressive melee/ac/hp, shadowknights are veritable juggernauts in PVP, with enough arsenal to annihilate 2-3 rogues in a row if you give them the chance.<br>
<br>
Solution - don't give them the chance.  Just like with necros, the battle goes in their favor the longer they have to use their options against you, while your options are best used at the beginning of a fight.  Lead off with blind poison against an inexperienced target, or snare against a more experienced one (experienced players will run in a straight line until blindness wears off, jbooting as they go).  Snare, on the other hand, limits the SK to two options - melee you (this is what you want) or shadowstep (you can interrupt it).  While shadowknight melee DOES hurt, and hurt a lot, a shadowknight meleeing you is a shadowknight that isn't jousting you.  Jack up your damage to full power right at the start, and you can annihilate an SK very quickly.  Open up with a duelist backstab right as he begins his first cast, and you'll do a LOT of damage very quickly, with a good chance at an interrupt besides.  If you don't have Duelist yet, use Deadeye - even better chance at an interrupt, but not as much damage.<br>
<br>
The trick in fighting a shadowknight is, like most other fights, to keep him under your control - you want him in your melee range as long as possible, preferably snared or otherwise disabled.  Once he gets loose of you, you've got a problem, and your best bet is to dispell all his buffs, hoping to get See Invis with it, and go stealth to backstab him when he tries to refresh it.  If he's got a permanent see invis item, your chances at this point are very low of winning.  Again, same rules as necros - don't let them lifetap and stay on them like a bloodthirsty hound.  The shadowknight you want to fight is the one that never gets a cast off. <p><b> -- Arafain Entreri, 60 Assassin<br> -- Arafein Soulstriker, 53 Champion...err, 52, die Vox!<br> -- Arafax Kokorozan, 20 Monk Giantfriend<br> -- Requiem of Souls<br> -- Formerly of The Rathe Server, now of Zebuxoruk<br></b><i>"Once, in the old west, a gentleman shot a professional gunfighter in the back. When asked why he didn't give the other chap a chance to draw, he replied, 'Well, he's dead and I'm alive and that's how I wanted it to be." -- from <u>Red Planet</u>, Robert A. Heinlein</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvenvensilentdagger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Venven Silentdagger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/1/01 1:17:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling a SK</span><hr size=1> This is how I would have done against a lvl 60 SK.<br>
<br>
Wear resist gear to resist his dot's and fear and snare.<br>
Make sure to inflict massive damage on him fast or he will win due to his lifetap spells and dot's on you, by using your duelist disc and timing in the backstab hits he will get very hurt.<br>
Wear regen items (Fungi Tunic, Belt of the Great Turtle etc) to counteract his dot's. Though.. I always wear as much regen items I can whenever I duel.<br>
<br>
That is some basic things, of course you need to be skilled in movement and timing of backstabs and hits to be able to inflict alot of damage on him fast, if you can't his dot's and lifetaps + HT will wear you down pretty fast. An sk is hard to duel, at least if the sk you duel play his char well.<br>
<br>
